        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 2:05PM EDT by NWS Morristown TN</headline>
        <description>At 205 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Ridgeside, or over Chattanooga, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Chattanooga, Rossville, Ridgeside, Harrison, South Cleveland,
Collegedale, East Brainerd, East Ridge, Apison, and Ooltewah.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
